# Software Product Management Plan

## 1. Project Overview
The Smart Study App is a software system designed to help university students manage their academic responsibilities effectively. The system provides tools for organising class schedules, tracking assignments, and planning study sessions — all in one centralised platform.

## 2. Product Vision
To provide a simple, integrated platform that helps students manage their academic workload, improve productivity, and achieve better academic performance.

## 3. Objectives
- Help students organise their academic activities in one place
- Reduce missed deadlines and improve time management
- Deliver a user-friendly and reliable system accessible on web and mobile

## 4. Target Users
- University and college students
- Students managing multiple courses and responsibilities

## 5. Scope

### In Scope
- Class schedule management
- Assignment tracking and deadline management
- Study session planning
- Notifications and reminders

### Out of Scope
- Financial management features
- Non-academic task management
- Social networking features

## 6. Product Roadmap

| Phase | Description | Timeline |
|-------|-------------|----------|
| Phase 1 | Product vision, wireframes, and repository setup | Week 1–3 |
| Phase 2 | Agile planning, sprint backlog, and team roles | Week 4–6 |
| Phase 3 | Feature identification, personas, and user stories | Week 7–9 |
| Phase 4 | Development, testing, and deployment | Week 10–14 |

## 7. Development Approach
The project will follow an **Agile (Scrum)** methodology, with iterative development and continuous feedback. Features will be delivered in increments across 2-week sprints, allowing flexibility and continuous improvement.

