## 9. Risk Management

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|--------|------------|
| Poor requirement understanding | Medium | High | Regular communication and feedback sessions |
| Delays in development | Medium | High | Incremental delivery and task prioritisation |
| Low user adoption | Low | High | Focus on usability and user-centred design |
| Technical issues / bugs | Medium | Medium | GitHub version control and code reviews |
| Team member unavailability | Low | Medium | Cross-training and task documentation |

## 10. Success Metrics
- Number of active registered users
- Assignment and task completion rates
- User engagement (daily and weekly active usage)
- User satisfaction feedback scores
- Reduction in missed deadlines reported by users

## 11. Release Plan
- **v1.0**: Initial release with core features (schedule and assignment tracking)
- **v1.1**: Study planner and notifications added
- **v1.2**: Performance improvements based on user feedback
- **v2.0**: Scaling, optimisation, and additional features

## 12. Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology | Reason |
|-------|-----------|--------|
| Frontend | React.js | Component-based, fast rendering, widely supported |
| Backend | Python / Django | Rapid development, strong REST API support, large community |
| Database | PostgreSQL | Reliable, scalable relational database suitable for academic data |
| Design | Figma | Industry-standard UI/UX prototyping tool |
| Version Control | GitHub | Industry-standard, supports collaboration and CI/CD |
| Communication | WhatsApp + Google Meet | Accessible and familiar to the team |
